radiographic_examinations.findings: A catheter projects over the left femoral region, presumed venous. Large central drainage catheter projects over the mid abdomen. In the left upper quadrant, there are 2 linear densities with associated adjacent rectangular densities, likely representing two towels, reportedly known to be left within the abdominal cavity. No other radiopaque foreign object is identified. Mild gaseous distention of multiple loops of bowel likely represents postoperative ileus.
